In March 1993 the Bombay Stock Exchange survived a wave of selling, governmental 
criticism, a bomb attack that killed at least 255 people, another bombing in Calcutta 
killing 45, and the looming threat of war and rioting to reverse the downward trend and 
head upward again.</SUM>
